@startuml usecase_wp4a
left to right direction

skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Maintenance Manager" as Manager
actor "Technician" as Technician
actor "Scheduler / System" as Scheduler

package "Maintenance Subsystem (WP4A)" {
    usecase "Create Maintenance Template" as UC_CreateTemplate
    usecase "Register Maintenance Part" as UC_CreatePart
    usecase "Create Maintenance Record" as UC_CreateRecord
    usecase "Update Record Status & Notes" as UC_UpdateRecord
    usecase "List / Search Maintenance Records" as UC_ListRecords
    usecase "Get Maintenance Totals / Reports" as UC_Totals
    usecase "Resolve Aircraft Model (name / id)" as UC_ResolveModel
}

Manager --> UC_CreateTemplate
Manager --> UC_CreatePart
Technician --> UC_CreateRecord
Technician --> UC_UpdateRecord
Manager --> UC_ListRecords
Scheduler --> UC_CreateRecord

UC_CreateTemplate .> UC_ResolveModel : <<include>>
UC_CreateRecord .> UC_ResolveModel : <<include>>
UC_ListRecords .> UC_Totals : <<extend>>

note right of UC_CreateTemplate
  Templates are associated to aircraft models
  (API accepts model names; use-case resolves to domain entities)
end note

note left of UC_UpdateRecord
  Updates enforce optimistic locking using ETag / If-Match
end note

@enduml

